## **Use time-bound admin access**

Administrative access must only be granted on a time-limited basis. You must provide a clear justification, a specific scope, and an expiry date. A team lead or security approver must approve the request.

Use time-bound mechanisms like short-lived Personal Access Tokens (PATs) or automated role expirations. Access must be revoked automatically when it expires. If you need an extension, you must submit a new justification.
